  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Polymyxin B hemoperfusion (PMX-HP) is mainly used to remove endotoxins in septic shock
      patients with intra-abdominal infections. Because of the concerns of postoperative bleeding,
      physicians may hesitate to use anticoagulation in patients with septic shock within a few
      hours after an abdominal operation. We developed a heparin dosing score protocol for heparin
      dosage adjustment. The purpose of the study is to examine the safety and efficacy of the
      heparin dosing score protocol.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
